Full i18n audit and correction for PhotoVault

You are working on a React + Firebase app called PhotoVault, located in `/src/`. The project already includes multi-language support with i18next and `react-i18next`. There are JSON language files for English (`/locales/en/`) and Norwegian (`/locales/no/`), including: `translation.json`, `common.json`, `albums.json`, and `security.json`.

🎯 Objective Ensure 100% translation coverage - every visible text must use t() keys. No hardcoded strings in JSX.

⚙️ What you must do

1. Scan all `.jsx` and `.js` files under `/src/` (components, pages, contexts, utils)
2. Find ALL hardcoded text strings in JSX/JS
3. Replace with proper t() calls using existing or new keys
4. Add missing keys to BOTH en/ and no/ JSON files with proper translations
5. Ensure correct useTranslation imports with right namespaces
6. Fix date formatting to use i18n.language for locale switching
7. At the END, provide a brief summary of changes made

⚠️ Important rules

- Keep existing key naming conventions (buttons._, notifications._, etc.)
- Use plural forms where needed: "key" and "key_plural"
- Maintain all JSX formatting and variable interpolations
- Add keys to the most logical JSON file (common for shared, albums for album-specific, etc.)
- Provide quality Norwegian translations (not just Google Translate)

🚀 Execute all changes automatically. Summary at the end only.

